<b>How do you make those videos?</b>
<p><font color=red>On various Sonic the Hedgehog-related pages, including Sonic HQ, The Sonic Foundation, and Knothole Express, I have observed downloads of images, sounds, RealVideo episodes, AVI (Video for Windows) movies, etc.  However, I really have wondered how the downloads of the Saturday morning episodes (SatAM) were created--that is, how does one actually manage to put images, sounds, RealVideo clips, and movies of an animated cartoon for television?  This inquiry poses quite a puzzle to me, and I would greatly appreciate it if you would clarify this matter.   Feel free to explain your answer in somewhat technical detail, since I am quite computer literate, my knowledge ranging from simple computer operations to computer programming in the languages of BASIC (Beginner's All-Purpose Symbolic Instruction Code) and Visual Basic.  (I also have had a sprinkling of experience with JavaScript.)  However, please keep in mind that I have had no experience in creating sound or video files (including RealVideo), nor any expert experience with image editing.  (I can use an image-editing utility such as Paint or Paint Shop Pro to create or edit existing pictures.)   </font>
<p>Hm, sorry to tell you this, but I have <I>no</I> clue! You see, we didn't even create those videos. We got them (yes, with permission ^__^ ) from another site. All I know is it requires some sort of special video cable. Sorry! 
 - Stumped Joey
</font></td></tr></table>

<p><table width=100% border=1 cellspacing=0 bordercolorlight=blue bordercolordark=23238E>
<tr><td bgcolor=000000><font face="Franklin Gothic Medium, Verdana" size=-1>
<b>The Story of Chaos</b>
<p><font color=red>I have a question related to the storyline of  Sonic Adventure:   I don't understand the story behind Chaos, the Master Emerald, and Tikal.  Can you please explain it to me? Thanks!   p.s: you guys have a great website!  </font>
<p>Ok- Chaos was a protector of the Chao Babies and the Master Emerald (See? They <I>do</I> have something to do with the storyline!). Soon, Tikal's father and his minions went to take control of the Master Emerald's power, but when they tried to do so- Chaos appeared. Chaos then took the power of all seven Chaos Emeralds, and became Perfect Chaos. Then, Perfect Chaos destroyed civilization as they knew it. After the destruction, Tikal (somehow) trapped Chaos as well as herself inside the Master Emerald, and you know they were in there until disturbed by Dr. Robotnik. So, it's kinda complicated. Thanks for your compliments! 
 - The Weirdo Joey
</font></td></tr></table>

</td></tr></table>

